Full Description: BitLaw is a comprehensive Internet resource on technology and intellectual property law. In this site, you will find complete copies of the United States Patent, Copyright, and Trademark statutes, as well as the relevant regulations from the Code of Federal Regulations. BitLaw also includes converted versions of the TMEP and MPEP (the office manuals created by the United States Trademark and Patent Offices, respectively). Each of these documents include links to the relevant statutory and regulatory sections. Finally, BitLaw contains a great deal of custom written descriptions of how these areas of the law affect the computer and technology industries. While some of this information is available elsewhere on the Internet, the goal of BitLaw is to bring this information together, in a convenient and inter-linked format. Beck and Tysver To assist in this goal, BitLaw's search capabilities have been upgraded using the Google Custom Search service. The search bar is found at the bottom of every page. Search results can now be narrowed on the results page, so that only statutes or regulations are searched for your terms. Similarly, searches can be restricted to the MPEP, the TMEP, or to the BitLaw legal summaries. BitLaw was created by Daniel A. Tysver, a partner with the Minneapolis patent law firm of Beck & Tysver. Our firm provides patent and trademark legal services to clients from around the world, ranging from individual inventors and start-up companies to Fortune 100 companies. Please consider using our firm if you are in need of intellectual property legal services.

Description: The Funding Farm brings business, products and ideas together with investors from Rural America.
Full Description: The Funding Farm brings business, products and ideas together with investors from Rural America. Don’t be fooled…corn farmers in South Dakota, Iowa and Minnesota generate billions of dollars in wealth each and every year and they want to see new ideas, products and companies GROW! The Funding Farm is owned by accredited investors from Rural America who want to turn concepts into reality, start new businesses and grow existing businesses. Through its member owners, The Funding Farm has access to funding and expertise that can help our clients to be successful. The Funding Farm fully embraces its Midwestern roots: we are looking primarily for Midwestern companies that want to work with Midwestern investors. When you work with The Funding Farm you will get access to us and to our network of accredited investors as potential partners and backers. You will feel like and be treated like you are at our kitchen table. But our kitchen table has seats for 1,000’s of accredited investors who want to look at your concept, product or company! The Funding Farm was created in response to a need to tap sources of wealth in Rural America that want to participate in helping re-build America and its economy without relying on Government support. Its unique structure will allow farmers, rural Americans and indeed all Midwesterners to participate in taking good ideas to commercial reality and building existing companies without sending their money to a money manager on the east or west coast that does not care about our local economy, communities or people. Investors will hold their money until they are ready to invest it…investment decisions will be made by the owner member, not the “fund manager”! The Funding Farm is looking primarily for Midwest American companies (or companies willing to move to the Midwest), particularly renewable energy, agricultural, manufacturing, green and technology-driven enterprises. The Funding Farm empowers its clients to build successful businesses by providing them with high quality early, middle and late-stage business development, funding, and implementation assistance from a single, local source. It is managed by a core group of professional managers and is owned by accredited investor owner-members who are all interested in making investments in the long term success of new and developing companies.

Description: KidsCash is an e-wallet for kids that allows them to buy goods online independently, and educates them on saving and spending.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: KidsCash is an e-wallet for kids. It is safe, easy and fun. It educates kids of all ages about saving and spending, and lets them purchase goods online independently, without the need of an adult payment option. Online shopping experience is changing dramatically with the introduction of online goods and virtual goods. The dependency on the adult payment option is bothering both parents and children. Many online stores are losing customers because “Children don’t click the add to cart button”. With KidsCash, children can easily and securely shop online. Parents can rest assure and not be bothered with the child every whim, and still be fully involved with their behavior online. Merchants can integrate a “Pay with KidsCash” button in their sites in 2 minutes and get new customers and sales instantly. In the process children learn in a safe, controlled environment, how to be money-wise. KidsCash beats other payment methods by providing a simple solution for kids while supporting a line of values that exists in KidsCash alone.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Community and Lifestyle
